# This file was missing entirely, which caused a real bug: with no
# .dockerignore, `docker compose build` sends the ENTIRE project directory
# as build context, including frontend/node_modules if it happens to exist
# locally (e.g. from running `npm ci` outside Docker, or — as actually
# happened — from a node_modules bundled into a project zip built on a
# different OS/libc than the Alpine-based frontend-builder stage).
#
# The Dockerfile's frontend-builder stage does `npm ci` correctly inside
# the container, but its later `COPY frontend/ .` step then copies the
# local (potentially foreign-OS) node_modules right on top of the
# freshly-installed one, corrupting binary symlinks like node_modules/
# .bin/tsc. Symptom: "Error: Cannot find module '../lib/tsc.js'" during
# `npm run build`, immediately after a successful `npm ci`.

# Dependencies — always reinstalled inside each build stage, never wanted
# from the host or a bundled copy.
node_modules
frontend/node_modules
**/node_modules

# Go build artifacts — irrelevant to the build context, just bloat it.
bin/
*.exe
*.test

# VCS metadata — not needed inside the image, and .git can be large.
.git
.gitignore

# Local secrets — never send these into a build context.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Editor/OS cruft.
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
.DS_Store

# Logs and local scratch files.
*.log
build.log
